#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ckeystrokes_for_windows_explorer-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h1:17-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\keystrokes_for_windows_explorer-an.htm+html.body.h1:17-1"
msgid "Additional Notes on Keystrokes for Working in Windows Explorer"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ckeystrokes_for_windows_explorer-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:18-1
msgid "Delete Selected File or Folder (DELETE)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ckeystrokes_for_windows_explorer-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:19-1
msgid ""
"When deleting a file, you may be prompted to confirm that this is what you wish "
"to do."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ckeystrokes_for_windows_explorer-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:20-1
msgid "Rename Selected File or Folder (F2)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ckeystrokes_for_windows_explorer-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:21-1
msgid ""
"If Windows is configured to hide file extensions for known file types, you will "
"not be able to change file extensions for these files. When file extensions are "
"displayed and you change them, you may get a warning message. This is because the "
"file extension determines which application will open certain types of files."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ckeystrokes_for_windows_explorer-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:22-1
msgid "Refresh Window (F5)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ckeystrokes_for_windows_explorer-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:23-1
msgid ""
"Use this keystroke if changes you have made do not seem to be reflected in what "
"JAWS is indicating."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ckeystrokes_for_windows_explorer-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:24-1
msgid "Switch Between Tree View and List View (F6 or TAB)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ckeystrokes_for_windows_explorer-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:25-1
msgid ""
"This keystroke switches focus between the available views. If the Address Bar and "
"Toolbar are displayed, they are included in this \"switch to\" cycle."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ckeystrokes_for_windows_explorer-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:26-1
msgid "Go Up One Folder Level (BACKSPACE)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ckeystrokes_for_windows_explorer-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:27-1
msgid ""
"The keystroke will move you to the previous level in the tree view. When you move "
"back to that level the item you land on will not be selected, use the "
"<b>SPACEBAR</b> to select it."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ckeystrokes_for_windows_explorer-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:28-1
msgid "Open File or Folder Properties (ALT+ENTER)"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Ckeystrokes_for_windows_explorer-an.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:29-1
msgid ""
"Properties of files and folders will give you different information depending on "
"the kind of file or folder you are requesting information for. If you look at the "
"properties for a folder like My Documents, you will find out information such as "
"the size and location of the folder as well as the attributes. If you get the "
"properties for a shortcut, you can find out the location of the original file. "
"Document properties will also tell you the name, location, and size, in addition "
"to the author and the title. The properties for items in Windows Explorer "
"encompass a wide range of possibilities."
msgstr ""

